				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think it is a good idea to make a Bad Apple demo for the SNES, to compete with the Genesis demo.<br /><br />If the SNES demo video runs at 30fps fullscreen 2bpp, then it would take 7kB of DMA per frame.  Since we do not need to use the OAM for this demo, we can DMA up to 6kB of data per frame.  In order to fit 7kB of graphical patterns into 6kB, we can take advantage of solid colored tiles that are all black or all white.<br /><br />I could program the dma loading scheme and pack-to-planar conversion, but I don't know how to do the video encoding part.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

