				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Motion vectors is kind of overkill. Just check which tiles are changed (with amount threshold optionally) between frames, store them somehow efficiently enough, put the new tiles over previously decoded frame.<br /><br />A dictionary I was talking about could contain not only solid colors, but also some common blocks, or blocks that could replace a number of similar looking blocks (this reduces quality, but saves room). Like, almost solid tile without few corner pixels, etc. Staticstics of common blocks could be collected from source frames before compression.</div>

